        <p>Directives are special instructions that tell Blazor how to handle components and elements.</p>
        
        <div class="tutorial-directive-grid">
            <div class="tutorial-directive-card">
                <h4>@@page</h4>
                <p>Defines a route for the component</p>
                <code>@@page "/courses"</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tutorial-directive-card">
                <h4>@@inject</h4>
                <p>Injects a service via dependency injection</p>
                <code>@@inject CourseService Service</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tutorial-directive-card">
                <h4>@@implements</h4>
                <p>Implements an interface</p>
                <code>@@implements IDisposable</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tutorial-directive-card">
                <h4>@@inherits</h4>
                <p>Inherits from a base class</p>
                <code>@@inherits ComponentBase</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tutorial-directive-card">
                <h4>@@rendermode</h4>
                <p>Sets the component's render mode</p>
                <code>@@rendermode InteractiveServer</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="tutorial-directive-card">
                <h4>@@attribute</h4>
                <p>Applies an attribute to the component</p>
                <code>@@attribute [Authorize]</code>
            </div>
        </div>

